sql:
SELECT COUNT(*)
FROM analytics_data
WHERE c2_int > 1000;

SELECT id, c5_double
FROM analytics_data
WHERE c9_bool = 1;

SELECT source_id, COUNT(*) 
FROM scheduled_jobs 
GROUP BY source_id;

external_knowledge:
- "new records" refers to entries in the analytics_data table created after the manager's last login;
- "departments" relate to departments overseeing activities logged in the analytics_data table;
- "more than a thousand" means a count greater than 1000.

- "bustling with activity" metaphorically means having a lot of members or records;
- "more than a dozen members" refers to having more than 10 records;
- "activity in terms of record count" means the number of records each department has.

